 The Minister of Transportation, Hon. Rotimi Amaechi has been appointed as the Director-General of President Muhammadu Buhari’s Campaign Organisation for the coming 2019 presidential election. This was made known in a statement signed by the President’s Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Malam Garba Shehu, in Abuja on Thursday. Amaechi was also the Director-General of the Buhari-Osinbajo Presidential Campaign Committee in 2014-2015 that won the elections and brought the current administration into office. Shehu disclosed that the new Director-General will announce other appointments into the campaign structure as approved by the President. 